wiki.content: Dazed and Confused is the biggest hit from the debut (and break through) album of Led Zeppelin released 12th january, 1969. This song and album became music history. It is still considered a huge hit by many people. According to the Dazed and Confused Songfacts, it was inspired by an acoustic song that Jimmy Page heard folk singer Jake Holmes perform. Holmes version was about an acid trip, but contained many of the same elements that made their way into the Led Zeppelin version. In concert, Led Zeppelin would play and extended version of this song which would sometimes run as long as 30 minutes. It was a showcase for the amazing guitar wizardry of Jimmy Page, and they never played it quite the same twice.
